    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Spider Pentapeptide-1 is a single chain peptide consisting of glycine, proline and serine. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from Major Ampullate Spidroin 2 found in the spider, Argiope aurantia. The parent protein contains a maximum of 349 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence from the 20 standard amino acids."
